      {
        "id": 1946987,
        "name": "Brian Heslop",
        "username": "Brian_Heslop",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/brian_heslop/{size}/2307_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-06-08T19:05:42.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>We opened up four or five Ramonet over harvest, three in one night because they all seemed far too tight - from successively older vintages starting with 12, then 11, then 10. None of them really blossomed until the next day when they were fantastic and matched with your tasting note but with a more expressive nose.</p>\n<p>Did you happen to try it the day after?</p>",
