      {
        "id": 1947077,
        "name": "Barry Rothof",
        "username": "Barry_Rothof",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/barry_rothof/{size}/1215_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-06-08T21:36:14.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Had the 2013 Domaine Ramonet Chassagne-Montrachet 1er Cru Les Vergers recently; rich, assertive and concentrated with great strength and vibrancy. The 2014 Jean-Claude Ramonet Chassagne-Montrachet was full of charm and flesh, with bright acidity, underlying minerality and good length. Overall, the Ramonet wines are admirable and relatively forward.</p>\n<p>New (negoce?) wines from Jean-Claude Ramonet ; 2014 Chassagne-Montrachet 1er Cru \u201cClos du Cailleret\u201d and 2014 Saint-Aubin 1e Cru \u201cLes Murgers des Dents de Chien\u201d - One of the best value for a white from the C\u00f4te de Beaune.</p>",
